uientry.unicode: With this setting enabled distant hill silhouettes are smoother and less prone to popping as the camera moves.||It also enables very high quality displacement mapping for objects such as rocks and boulders.

uientry.unicode: Enabling soft shadows effectively blurs the outlines of shadows, which can look very pixelated from certain camera angles.||Shadows are more expensive to render with this option enabled, but the results are much more realistic.

uientry.unicode: Screen-space ambient occlusion||Check this to simulate ambient lighting and shadows around the edges of objects.||If your game is running slow you may want to uncheck this.

High dynamic range effect||Check this to turn on light bloom effects.||Bloom recreates the effect of strong light sources bleeding around objects.||If your game is running slow you may want to uncheck this.
